conclusion: Understanding interaction between objects A and B with blocks C, D, E, and F.
Objects A and B are placed on the table.
Blocks C, D, E, and F are positioned on the table.
Objects A and B move through the air and land on the table, coming into contact with the blocks.
Blocks are likely to be affected by the contact between objects A and B.
Blocks may be pushed or moved in response to the contact.
Blocks will be pushed to the side.
